Date your partner. Compliment your partner. Don’t ever get comfortable because it’s been awhile. Quickest way to lose someone is to stop doing the things you did to get them. Always keep it going.
If you find someone who makes you smile, who checks up on you often to see if you’re okay, who watches out for you and wants the very best for you, don’t let them go. Keep them close and don’t take them for granted. People like them are hard to find.

I don’t know who needs to hear this but, if people wanted to, they would. If someone wants to fix their relationship with you, they put in the effort to have uncomfortable conversations. If someone wants to love you, they put in the effort to love you the way you need to be loved. If someone wants to be part of your life, they put in the effort to be part of your life. It’s that simple. You just don’t want to accept any of that because that means feeling the hurt & rejection of realizing some people just don’t care about you the way you care for them. & for that, my heart goes out to you. But my love, rejection is part of life & necessary for growth. & the sooner you accept the situation, the sooner you can move on to learning & applying the lesson in all of this: you deserve to have people in your life that care to communicate, understand, love, & put in work for you.
